## How to Run the Network Sniffer

1. Open Terminal in Kali Linux.
2. Make sure Python3 is installed:
   ```bash
   python3 --version

Install Scapy library (if not installed):

sudo pip3 install scapy
Save the sniffer code as sniffer.py.

Run the sniffer with root privileges:

sudo python3 sniffer.py
Open a browser or perform network activity to see live packets.
Press Ctrl+C to stop the sniffer.
